# Complete Resume & Cover Letter Generation System
## Master Reference — Every File, Every Scenario, Every Flow

---

## 1. Directory Architecture (What Lives Where)

```
ats-job-search/                          ← Project Root
│
├── automation/
│   └── Generate-Application.ps1        ← PowerShell script (PHASE 1: Scaffold)
│
├── .agent/workflows/
│   └── generate-application.md         ← /generate-application slash command (4-step runbook)
│
├── Project_Assets/                      ← Master Templates & Reference Docs (NEVER EDIT PER-APPLICATION)
│   ├── resume_template.tex             ← LuaLaTeX resume base (copied & tailored per application)
│   ├── cover_letter_template.tex       ← LuaLaTeX cover letter base (copied & tailored per application)
│   ├── AI_Career_Strategy_Prompt.md    ← Master AI prompt (582 lines — the brain of the entire system)
│   ├── ATS_Document_Engineering_2026.md← ATS technical compliance reference (5 gates)
│   ├── Resume_Length_Strategy_2026.md  ← 4-phase research protocol for 1-page vs 2-page decision
│   ├── Cover_Letter_Standards_2026.md  ← Cover letter structure, paragraph templates, scoring
│   └── 2026_Application_Standards.md  ← Summary standards doc (inside Project_Assets/)
│
├── 2026_Application_Standards.md       ← Root-level copy (also copied per-application by the script)
│
└── Applications/
    └── Feb24/                          ← Date-grouped (MMMdd format)
        └── Company_JobTitle/           ← One folder per application (auto-created by script)
            ├── job_description.md      ← You paste the JD here
            ├── jobtitle_resume.tex     ← Tailored resume (you paste AI output here)
            ├── jobtitle_coverletter.tex← Tailored cover letter (you paste AI output here)
            ├── README.md               ← Hiring manager snapshot (AI-generated)
            ├── AI_Career_Strategy_Prompt.md    ← Copy (reference while tailoring)
            ├── ATS_Document_Engineering_2026.md← Copy (reference while checking)
            ├── Resume_Length_Strategy_2026.md  ← Copy (reference during length decision)
            ├── Cover_Letter_Standards_2026.md  ← Copy (reference during CL writing)
            └── 2026_Application_Standards.md   ← Copy (reference during compilation)
```

> **Key design principle:** The `Project_Assets/` folder is your single source of truth. The PowerShell script copies everything into the per-application folder so all reference docs are self-contained with the application.

