## 6. Phase 4 — LaTeX Compilation

### The LaTeX Template Architecture

**resume_template.tex structure:**

```latex
% Must be FIRST — before \documentclass
\DocumentMetadata{
    tagging=on,
    pdfstandard=ua-2,
    lang=en-US,
    tagging-setup = {math/setup={mathml-SE}}
}
\documentclass[letterpaper,10pt]{article}

% Core packages:
\usepackage{unicode-math}     % semantic math tagging
\usepackage[empty]{fullpage}  % full-page layout
\usepackage{titlesec}         % section formatting
\usepackage[hidelinks]{hyperref} % accessible links + PDF metadata
\usepackage{tabularx}         % skills table
\usepackage{float}            % reading-order lock for tables
\usepackage{enumitem}         % bullet formatting
\usepackage[english]{babel}

% Geometry: adds 1 inch of usable text area (expands margins)
\addtolength{\oddsidemargin}{-0.5in}
\addtolength{\evensidemargin}{-0.5in}
\addtolength{\textwidth}{1.0in}
\addtolength{\topmargin}{-.5in}
\addtolength{\textheight}{1.0in}

% Section dividers with horizontal rule
\titleformat{\section}{\large\bfseries}{}{0em}{}[\titlerule]
\titlespacing{\section}{0pt}{12pt}{6pt}
```

**cover_letter_template.tex structure:**

```latex
\DocumentMetadata{tagging=on, pdfstandard=ua-2, lang=en-US}
\documentclass[letterpaper,10pt]{article}
\usepackage{fontspec}           % LuaLaTeX font system
\usepackage[margin=1in]{geometry}
\usepackage{hyperref}
\usepackage{parskip}            % paragraph spacing (no indent)
```

### Compile Command

```bash
# From inside the application folder:
lualatex [jobtitle]_resume.tex
lualatex [jobtitle]_coverletter.tex
```

> **Must use LuaLaTeX — never pdfLaTeX or XeLaTeX.** The `\DocumentMetadata`, `unicode-math`, and `fontspec` packages are LuaLaTeX-only.

---

## 7. The 5 ATS Validation Gates (Pre-Submission Safety Checks)

Every document must pass all 5 gates before it is considered ready to submit. This is documented in `ATS_Document_Engineering_2026.md`.

### Why This Matters — 2026 ATS Statistics

- **~87%** of organizations use AI-driven screening
- **~75%** of resumes are rejected before a human sees them
- **~43%** of parsing failures are caused by formatting errors alone
- **~88%** of resumes with graphics, icons, or multi-column tables are discarded

### Gate 1: Compilation Safety ✓

- [ ] Compiled with **LuaLaTeX** (not pdfLaTeX, not XeLaTeX)
- [ ] `\DocumentMetadata{lang=en-US, pdfstandard=ua-2, tagging=on}` is present and appears **before** `\documentclass`
- [ ] Zero LaTeX errors on final compile (non-stop mode is not acceptable for final output)
- [ ] `\hypersetup` includes correct `author`, `title`, and `keywords` metadata

### Gate 2: Syntactic / Parsing Safety ✓

Every special character must be escaped in LaTeX:

| Identifier | LaTeX | Why |
|------------|-------|-----|
| `C#` | `C\#` | Bare `#` = macro parameter error |
| `M&A` | `M\&A` | Bare `&` = table field delimiter error |
| `R&D` | `R\&D` | Same as above |
| `50%` | `50\%` | Bare `%` = comment character in LaTeX |
| `S&P` | `S\&P` | Same as M&A |

Also:
- [ ] No forced line breaks (`\\`) inside semantic content (experience bullets, summary)
- [ ] No text boxes, floating sidebars, or table-based experience sections
- [ ] Contact info must be in the **document body** — not headers/footers

### Gate 3: Reading Order Safety ✓

- [ ] **Single-column layout only** for ATS submission
  - Multi-column = parser reads columns sequentially, disconnecting job titles from descriptions
- [ ] **The Notepad Test:** Copy-paste the PDF text into Notepad. If reading order is coherent (not column-interleaved), document is safe
- [ ] `pdftotext [resume].pdf -` reads top-to-bottom without fragmentation
- [ ] Standard section headings only:
  - ✅ `Professional Experience`, `Work Experience`, `Education`, `Skills`, `Certifications`
  - ❌ `Where I've Been`, `Academic Journey`, `My Toolkit`

### Gate 4: Semantic Quality ✓

ATS scoring weights (2026):

| Metric | Weight | What It Checks |
|--------|--------|----------------|
| Keywords/Skills Match | **40%** | Exact match + semantic variation density |
| Experience Relevance | **25%** | Career trajectory and industry context alignment |
| Job Title/Seniority | **10%** | Progression toward target role complexity |
| Education/Certifications | **10%** | Credential verification |
| Recency/Seniority | **10%** | Skills used in last 24 months weighted higher |
| Document Structure | **5%** | Machine-readability and section demarcation |

- [ ] Every bullet follows F-pattern: metric or scope in the **first 3 words**
- [ ] No buzzword chains without STAR evidence (scores ~0.44 — rejected; STAR scores ~0.76 — top band)
- [ ] Skills in the Skills block **also appear** in experience bullets with context
- [ ] Max 15–25 skills in Skills section (50+ triggers "keyword stuffing" AI detection)

### Gate 5: Accessibility Compliance (PDF/UA-2) ✓

Standard: **ISO 14289-2** (released March 2024) built on PDF 2.0

- [ ] All text is selectable (never submit a scanned/image-based PDF)
- [ ] Do NOT apply Adobe Acrobat's "Auto-tagging" — it overwrites LaTeX's semantic tags with generic inaccessible ones
- [ ] For high-stakes applications: validate with **veraPDF** or **PAC 2024**
- [ ] Font must have a complete **ToUnicode CMap** (LuaLaTeX with `tagging=on` guarantees this)

> **Why PDF/UA-2 matters for ATS:** Many multinational firms use unified ATS platforms across EU/US offices. Since June 2025 (European Accessibility Act), PDF/UA-2 is mandatory in the EU. These platforms default to the EU standard globally. A properly tagged LuaLaTeX document is the safest universal choice.

