## 11. Key Design Principles (Why the System Works This Way)

| Principle | What It Means |
|-----------|--------------|
| **"Risk-Owned Payloads"** | Every bullet shows Agency — you didn't just do tasks, you owned outcomes under uncertain conditions |
| **"Risk Architect" framing** | Identify failure modes → own the debugging path → deliver measurable improvements |
| **F-Pattern bullet structure** | Recruiters scan left-to-right, top-to-bottom; metric in first 3 words catches the eye before they scroll away |
| **Zero-party data rule** | Every metric in the cover letter must be a real number you inject (%, $, time savings) — not AI-hallucinated |
| **Golden Thread** | One unifying narrative connects your entire history to the role; appears in summary, bullets, README, and cover letter |
| **Semantic variations** | Don't repeat JD keywords verbatim >2x — use related terms instead; ATS semantic parsers score variations higher |
| **Single-column LaTeX** | Multi-column layouts cause ATS to read columns sequentially, disconnecting job titles from their descriptions |
| **LuaLaTeX mandatory** | Only LuaLaTeX supports `\DocumentMetadata`, `unicode-math`, and `fontspec` — required for PDF/UA-2 and correct ToUnicode CMap |
| **Language escaping** | `C\#`, `M\&A`, `R\&D`, `50\%` — bare special chars in LaTeX break compilation or OCR extraction |
| **15–25 skills max** | 50+ skills without STAR context = AI flags as keyword stuffing; focused list scores higher |

---

## 12. Common Failure Scenarios & How the System Prevents Them

| Failure | Prevention |
|---------|-----------|
| ATS rejects resume for formatting | Single-column LaTeX + PDF/UA-2 + Notepad Test |
| PDF text becomes garbled after copy-paste | LuaLaTeX ToUnicode CMap (e.g., "file" doesn't become "le") |
| LaTeX compile error on `C#` | `AI_Career_Strategy_Prompt.md` explicitly instructs: use `C\#` |
| LaTeX compile error on `&` | Prompt instructs: use `\&` for all ampersands |
| Wrong compiler used | All templates have `% COMPILER: LuaLaTeX` comment at top |
| Resume too long/short | 4-phase research protocol in `Resume_Length_Strategy_2026.md` runs before any writing |
| Cover letter feels generic | Business-need hook requires JD-specific company research (not mission statement) |
| Skills listed without evidence | Gate 4 check: every skill must appear in experience bullets with a result |
| AI-generated text flagged | Humanization directive in prompt prevents robotic transitions / perfectly uniform sentence structures |
| Wrong story selected for cover letter | Proof story selection table maps JD priority → specific story automatically |
| Multi-column breaks ATS | Template is single-column only; no tables in experience section |
| Header/footer contact info lost | Prompt and template both enforce: contact info in document BODY only |

---

## 13. The Full File Flow at a Glance

```
YOU RUN:
  .\automation\Generate-Application.ps1 -JobTitle "SWE" -Company "SpaceX"

  → Applications/Feb24/SpaceX_SWE/ is created with 9 files

YOU DO:
  Paste full JD into job_description.md

YOU DO:
  Copy AI_Career_Strategy_Prompt.md
  Fill in: Role, Company, JD, Current Resume
  Paste into AI (Gemini / GPT / Claude)

AI REASONS (internally):
  Phase 1: JD archetype = Defense/Aerospace → 2 page signal
  Phase 2: Levels.fyi shows L5 equivalent → 2 page signal
  Phase 3: Glassdoor shows "lack of depth" rejections → 2 page signal
  Phase 4: FINAL = 2 PAGES (override triggered)
  JD signals: Heisenbugs, race conditions, distributed systems, CUDA, C++
  Golden Thread: "Scalable Autonomy Systems Builder"

AI WRITES:
  spaceX_swe_resume.tex   (2-page, SpaceX signals: Heisenbugs, race conditions)
  spaceX_swe_coverletter.tex (Vibrating Agent story in P2; first-principles tone)
  README.md               (3 bullets from RL/robotics + distributed systems)

YOU DO:
  Paste .tex content into the copied template files
  Run: lualatex spaceX_swe_resume.tex
  Run: lualatex spaceX_swe_coverletter.tex

YOU CHECK:
  ✓ Gate 1: Compiled with zero errors
  ✓ Gate 2: C\# escaped, no \\ in bullets
  ✓ Gate 3: Notepad test passes (linear reading order)
  ✓ Gate 4: Every bullet front-loads metric; 20 skills with STAR evidence
  ✓ Gate 5: veraPDF shows 0 critical PDF/UA-2 errors

YOU SUBMIT:
  spaceX_swe_resume.pdf + spaceX_swe_coverletter.pdf
```

